Foliage

yesterday, we dragged the hours long
in our Milanese Airbnb.
stayed talking in your wilderness
instead of surrendering to sleep shifts

i thought i found my own oasis -- not knowing i'm still weak:
from the shine off your high laughing cheekbones
to your scoff, when i make myself insufferable for you.
weak beneath your eyes, staring back at mine

those eyes.
who say they're brown unless i dive in
to find the lurking green.

and just as i begin to cultivate this garden,
i'm stuck watching you disppear.
down a street crowded with dirty brick buildings
my feet anchored, eyes strained
you're in sight and
i try to keep you